										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I really love it when alternative cues from soundtracks, like the one below, are leaked. It&#8217;s nice to hear &#8220;fresh&#8221; developments and explorations of themes, and some of the different aspects of the corresponding scene that the composer was trying to reflect, performed and recorded to the same standard as the original soundtrack. Personally, I think they should be officially released in a similar way to some of the other &#8220;behind the scenes&#8221; elements of films, like conceptual art and deleted scenes. They&#8217;d certainly make a better addition to the soundtrack album than the remixes that some albums inexplicably include.<br />
